dmtfMobileComputerMIF.name: dmtfMobileComputerMIF
dmtfMobileComputerMIF.contactinfo: DMTF Technical Advisory Committee Mailstop JF2-53 2111 N.E. 25th Avenue Hillsboro, OR 97124 Phone: +1 503 264-9300 Email: dmtf-info@dmtf.org
dmtfMobileComputerMIF.description: This MIB is a translation of the DMTF Mobile Computer MIF, based on the translation rules defined by the DMTF DMI to SNMP Mapping Standard, Version 1.0. DMI-based systems running a DMI-to-SNMP Mapping Agent provide the ability to access DMI component instrumentation via SNMP protocol operations.

operationalGroupIndex.name: operationalGroupIndex
operationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State table for this device.

securitySettings.name: securitySettings
securitySettings.description: Enum describing the current hardware security settings on this device.

dmtfPortableBatteryTable.name: dmtfPortableBatteryTable
dmtfPortableBatteryTable.description: This group defines general information about the portable battery(s) in the system

dmtfPortableBatteryEntry.name: dmtfPortableBatteryEntry
dmtfPortableBatteryEntry.description: This group defines general information about the portable battery(s) in the system

portableBatteryIndex.name: portableBatteryIndex
portableBatteryIndex.description: The index into the portable battery table.

portableBatteryManufacturer.name: portableBatteryManufacturer
portableBatteryManufacturer.description: The name of the company that manufactured the battery.

portableBatterySerialNumber.name: portableBatterySerialNumber
portableBatterySerialNumber.description: The serial number for this battery.

portableBatteryDeviceName.name: portableBatteryDeviceName
portableBatteryDeviceName.description: Device name for this battery. For instance, Duracell DR-36.

portableBatteryDeviceChemistry.name: portableBatteryDeviceChemistry
portableBatteryDeviceChemistry.description: The battery chemistry. For instance, Lithium-ion or Nickel metal hydride.

portableBatteryDesignCapacity.name: portableBatteryDesignCapacity
portableBatteryDesignCapacity.description: The design capacity of the battery in mWatt-hours. If this attribute is not supported, value = 0x80000000

portableBatteryDesignVoltage.name: portableBatteryDesignVoltage
portableBatteryDesignVoltage.description: The design voltage of the battery in mVolts. If this attribute is not supported, value = 0x80000000

smartBatteryVersion.name: smartBatteryVersion
smartBatteryVersion.description: The Smart Battery Data Specification version number supported by this battery. If the battery does not support this function, the value should be left blank.

fullChargeCapacity.name: fullChargeCapacity
fullChargeCapacity.description: The full charge capacity of the battery in mWatt-hours. Comparis n of this value to the battery Design Capacity determines when the battery requires replacement. The battery industry has defined a battery's end of life to be when the Full Charge Capacity falls below 80% of the Design Capacity. If this attribute is not supported, value = -1.

remainingCapacity.name: remainingCapacity
remainingCapacity.description: The battery's remaining capacity in mWatt-hours. This value is used with Design Capacity or Full Charge Capacity to calculate fuel gauge information. If this attribute is not supported, value = -1.

maximumError.name: maximumError
maximumError.description: The maximum error (as a percentage) in the Watt-hour data reported by the battery. The maximum error indicates the upper bound on how much additional energy the battery may have above the energy it reports having. When this value exceeds some value, for instance, 10%, some action must be taken (for instance, fully discharge then fully charge the battery) within some specified time (for instance, within two recharge cycles of the battery). If the action is not taken within the time frame, the error value

remainingBatteryTime.name: remainingBatteryTime
remainingBatteryTime.description: The remaining battery time in minutes, at the current average system power consumption level.

remainingTimeToFullBattery.name: remainingTimeToFullBattery
remainingTimeToFullBattery.description: The remaining time to charge the battery fully in minutes,at the current average system power consumption level and charging rate

powerUnitIndex.name: powerUnitIndex
powerUnitIndex.description: This is the ID of the Power Unit (logical portable battery) to which this Portable Battery belongs. This value matches up with the Power Unit Table Index attribute defined in the Power Unit Global Table.

dmtfPowerManagementTable.name: dmtfPowerManagementTable
dmtfPowerManagementTable.description: This group defines the power management state of components and groups within the system

dmtfPowerManagementEntry.name: dmtfPowerManagementEntry
dmtfPowerManagementEntry.description: This group defines the power management state of components and groups within the system

powerManagementEnabledDisabled.name: powerManagementEnabledDisabled
powerManagementEnabledDisabled.description: Enabled/Disabled state of power management on this device.

d1TimerValue.name: d1TimerValue
d1TimerValue.description: The time-out value in milliseconds to go from D0 (full ON) to D1 state. If D1 state is not supported the value is -1. If the transition is not controlled by a timer then the value is 0.

d2TimerValue.name: d2TimerValue
d2TimerValue.description: The time-out value in milliseconds to go from the next higher supported state (either D0 or D1) to the D2 state. If D2 state is not supporte the value is -1. If the transition is not controlled by a timer then the value is 0.

d3TimerValue.name: d3TimerValue
d3TimerValue.description: The time-out value in milliseconds to go from the next higher supported state (either D0, D1, or D2) to the D3 state. If D3 state is not supported the value is -1 meaning the device can never be turned off. If the transition is not controlled by a timer then the value is 0.

reducedCPUClockSpeed.name: reducedCPUClockSpeed
reducedCPUClockSpeed.description: Defines whether to enable CPU to slow down when possible

overrideAC.name: overrideAC
overrideAC.description: Enables/Disables power savings when AC is connected

ringEventResume.name: ringEventResume
ringEventResume.description: Enables system to resume operation when a modem ring occurs on a serial port or a wakeup occurs on a PC Card

alarmResume.name: alarmResume
alarmResume.description: Enables system to resume operation from suspend/standby mode at a time determined by an application program.

colorSupport.name: colorSupport
colorSupport.description: Defines whether the video output device supports color

contrast.name: contrast
contrast.description: The percentage (0-100) of total contrast of the videooutput device. If feature not available, value = 0x80000000

videoGroupReference.name: videoGroupReference
videoGroupReference.description: Defines the reference into the video group
